## Remarks  
<span data-ttu-id="df814-277">Die `Close` -Methode gibt sowohl nicht verwaltete als auch verwaltete Ressourcen frei, die zugeordnet sind <xref:System.Net.Sockets.NetworkStream> .</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="df814-277">The `Close` method frees both unmanaged and managed resources associated with the <xref:System.Net.Sockets.NetworkStream>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="df814-278">Wenn das den <xref:System.Net.Sockets.NetworkStream> zugrunde liegenden besitzt <xref:System.Net.Sockets.Socket> , wird es ebenfalls geschlossen.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="df814-278">If the <xref:System.Net.Sockets.NetworkStream> owns the underlying <xref:System.Net.Sockets.Socket>, it is closed as well.</span></span>

<span data-ttu-id="df814-279">Wenn ein einem <xref:System.Net.Sockets.NetworkStream> zugeordnet wurde <xref:System.Net.Sockets.TcpClient> , schließt die `Close` Methode die TCP-Verbindung, aber nicht die zugeordnete <xref:System.Net.Sockets.TcpClient> .</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="df814-279">If a <xref:System.Net.Sockets.NetworkStream> was associated with a <xref:System.Net.Sockets.TcpClient>, the `Close` method will close the TCP connection, but not dispose of the associated <xref:System.Net.Sockets.TcpClient>.</span></span>

## Examples  
<span data-ttu-id="df814-280">Im folgenden Codebeispiel wird die geschlossen <xref:System.Net.Sockets.NetworkStream> .</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="df814-280">The following code example closes the <xref:System.Net.Sockets.NetworkStream>.</span></span>

```vb
' Example for closing the NetworkStream.
' Close the NetworkStream
myNetworkStream.Close()
```

```csharp
// Example for closing the NetworkStream.

// Close the NetworkStream
myNetworkStream.Close();
```

```cpp
// Example for closing the NetworkStream.
// Close the NetworkStream
myNetworkStream->Close();
```
